{"word":"μάντις","slug":"μάντις","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>μάντις</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:μαίνομαι'><el>μαίνομαι</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>one who divines, a seer, prophet</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:—as <a href='S:feminine'>fem.</a> <i>a prophetess</i>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>a diviner, foreboder</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>a</i> kind of <i>grasshopper</i>, <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}